<body>
    <h1>Get Products</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"e2c52f5a95c9"><strong>Component type:</strong> Actio=
n</p>
<p local-id=3D"24db3f85fd1b"><strong>Category:</strong> Billing and Product=
s</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"f3ace29e36e8" id=3D"GetProducts-Overview">Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"359ebf27da07">The <strong>Get Products</strong> action retri=
eves all orderable products configured at your property. Products are items=
 or services that staff can add to a guest's bill =E2=80=94 for example, mi=
nibar items, extra pillows, or breakfast packages.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d21b97f57783">This component requires no input fields. It au=
tomatically uses your property's context to fetch the relevant products and=
 returns them as a list of items, each with a unique identifier and a displ=
ay name. When products belong to multiple services (e.g., "Accommodation" a=
nd "Spa"), the service name is appended to the product label for clarity.</=
p>
<p local-id=3D"32823ec5d1b6">The output is typically used to populate dropd=
own menus or to look up product identifiers in subsequent workflow steps =
=E2=80=94 for example, to post a specific product charge to a guest's bill.=
</p>
<hr local-id=3D"7a969ca5-28f1-4db5-8df0-9a10fbabbb70">
<h2 local-id=3D"9bb9f994aea1" id=3D"GetProducts-InputFields">Input Fields</=
h2>
<p local-id=3D"6b1ce33fe291">This component has <strong>no input fields</st=
rong>. It automatically retrieves all orderable products for the property a=
ssociated with the authenticated connection.</p>
<p local-id=3D"03b40f98716f"><strong>Note:</strong> The component uses the =
property context from your Mews automation connection. Make sure the connec=
tion is configured for the correct property before using this component.</p=
>
<hr local-id=3D"13d5c7e9-78c6-4443-ae89-4e1235b9614f">
<h2 local-id=3D"11192170a950" id=3D"GetProducts-OutputFields">Output Fields=
</h2>
<p local-id=3D"5c89aa0bfc04">When the products are successfully retrieved, =
the following data is available on the <strong>out</strong> output port as =
an array called <strong>Items</strong>:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"65=
85f286-7f0c-412c-a58d-56c092abe697" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"89bf8555-4371-407c-af92-3632776aee5f">
<th data-local-id=3D"7b26ddfd-c339-4d92-b925-a080da56f00e" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"433d0b2a8ea7">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"a801275e-1f05-4402-9364-dc6c4c15b62d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"0021b2a27c67">Type</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"5ab91cdf-a49c-4193-8586-d23b069d49a7" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"07dd3b8d9efe">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"cb61295e-370d-4d76-884a-6cddeac33781">
<td data-local-id=3D"bfbad346-a6b0-42e6-8284-0c89fd10ea29" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0a60cb088ee5"><strong>Value</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b83f6490-ede7-4ba4-9483-88c9f7961c1c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ce41b3d916ab">Text (GUID)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"1d51a90f-f6ea-4f9b-b067-6f9a4cfc2016" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"726371230816">The unique identifier of the product. Use this=
 value when referencing the product in other components (e.g., when posting=
 a product charge to a bill).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5cfdba35-e2c4-41fa-8d0b-c6a6450582a4">
<td data-local-id=3D"d99abf69-e717-4ae8-a3a1-d5e839f334f2" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c8b7faab3a51"><strong>Label</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ba5a24cb-1234-4b77-a33c-97acb7b337bf" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"370d390cff2e">Text</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"71879b61-5766-41f9-831b-94f99c52c627" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"edd8a29fa4b4">The display name of the product, localized to =
the property's default language. If products belong to more than one servic=
e, the service name is included in parentheses =E2=80=94 for example, <code=
>Breakfast (Restaurant)</code>. If all products belong to the same service,=
 only the product name is shown.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"1f5adb34b4eb" id=3D"GetProducts-OutputFormat">Output Format=
</h3>
<p local-id=3D"92c65c67ffd2">The output is an array of items. Each item con=
tains a <strong>Value</strong> and a <strong>Label</strong>. This format is=
 designed to be used directly with dropdown selectors and list-based compon=
ents in your workflows.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1330ba95fee3"><strong>Tip:</strong> You can connect the outp=
ut of this component to the input of other components that accept a product=
 selection =E2=80=94 for example, to let a workflow dynamically choose whic=
h product to post to a guest's bill.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"74e1edf4-4da6-4bb9-ba6f-da83978361c3">
<h2 local-id=3D"92c817d1dff4" id=3D"GetProducts-WhichProductsAreIncluded">W=
hich Products Are Included</h2>
<p local-id=3D"6c5d0dfacd4e">Not all products configured in your property a=
re returned. The component only retrieves products that meet <strong>all</s=
trong> of the following criteria:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"36ee5e4a-fad4-454a-8f9b-c79d9a38f7e5">
<li local-id=3D"0b3b2ff7-030d-4abe-b68a-fb7d901c713c">
<p local-id=3D"da2f7ae9c4af">The product belongs to an <strong>active servi=
ce</strong> at the property.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"70d37dc9-b954-4084-acc2-8a774af0b5e3">
<p local-id=3D"0df1987651f2">The product is <strong>not a default product</=
strong> (default products are automatically included in service orders and =
cannot be posted separately).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ceb11ec8-4696-4010-9738-314a0507afd7">
<p local-id=3D"86f69d72e786">The product is marked as <strong>orderable by =
employees</strong> (the "Offer to Employee" option is enabled in the produc=
t settings).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"94fe8db0-1791-4831-8ec4-e3bc7ff05a04">
<p local-id=3D"b58ba0a2f9b5">The product has <strong>not been deleted</stro=
ng>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"dcba01c04e29"><strong>Important:</strong> If you do not see =
an expected product in the output, verify that the product is set to "Offer=
 to Employee" in Mews Operations and that it belongs to an active service.<=
/p>
<hr local-id=3D"c1fd9c25-8a27-4911-8799-2c7be383f3ba">
<h2 local-id=3D"1dd55e9eead8" id=3D"GetProducts-Localization">Localization<=
/h2>
<p local-id=3D"e9f9d73b8140">Product and service names are returned in the =
property's default language. If a product name is not available in the defa=
ult language, the component falls back to English. If an English translatio=
n is also unavailable, the first available translation is used.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"eaeccf88-a82c-4bdc-bdb1-073feff27e53">
<h2 local-id=3D"b26beaef92b5" id=3D"GetProducts-HowItWorks">How It Works</h=
2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"ce88f730-0fb6-4fd6-94ef-f2230fefeb7b">
<li local-id=3D"d20ce313-e404-4f88-8dba-eb6c4c65d039">
<p local-id=3D"31c07a980578">The component is triggered by the previous ste=
p in the workflow (or manually).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c2533fd0-f17c-468d-9469-75aa6d20350c">
<p local-id=3D"3885004fb05a">A request is sent to retrieve all orderable pr=
oducts for the property associated with your connection.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"39dbc346-01be-4cbe-9008-e5e4eea02eec">
<p local-id=3D"01e56be8fa43">The system fetches active services at the prop=
erty and joins them with their non-default, employee-orderable products.</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"d92db218-5692-4210-ac92-499f46084c6d">
<p local-id=3D"abc6e02b3ffa">Product and service names are localized to the=
 property's default language.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"21455457-fd49-4a6c-b4f1-731120b540df">
<p local-id=3D"6156a85bc226">If products belong to more than one service, t=
he service name is appended to each product label in parentheses for disamb=
iguation.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3c5fab46-91ea-4737-9cb6-623f6a65c409">
<p local-id=3D"1f588532618b">The list of products (each with a unique ident=
ifier and display name) is sent to the <strong>out</strong> output port.</p=
></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"05ec5c53-e4fa-4d83-85f5-148c668d6a50">
<h2 local-id=3D"e1e140c42d6d" id=3D"GetProducts-ExampleUseCases">Example Us=
e Cases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"43f845b9-adec-4ccd-afbf-5eb4d2f5594f">
<li local-id=3D"1dd0cfec-909d-44b3-9fb6-a0cbfceec182">
<p local-id=3D"1a03d466d640"><strong>Dynamic product selection</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Use <strong>Get Products</strong> at the start of a workflow to popu=
late a product dropdown, allowing operators to select which product to post=
 to a guest's bill.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"72e8781a-1412-4217-87a5-e1143bee8470">
<p local-id=3D"4387729a6def"><strong>Automated upsell charging</strong> =E2=
=80=94 After a guest accepts an upsell offer (e.g., breakfast package), use=
 this component to look up the correct product identifier and then post the=
 charge automatically.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"08f11101-05c4-482b-b5ff-ae7cbcc2820c">
<p local-id=3D"469d9e237755"><strong>Product availability check</strong> =
=E2=80=94 Retrieve the current list of orderable products and compare it ag=
ainst expected items to verify that all required products are configured at=
 the property.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"4d52091e-008d-47a6-aa35-570e93057a14">
<h2 local-id=3D"8d3645a766e7" id=3D"GetProducts-Caching">Caching</h2>
<p local-id=3D"b9ff3866100b">The results of this component are <strong>cach=
ed</strong> per property to improve performance. If you have recently added=
 or modified products in Mews Operations, there may be a short delay before=
 the changes appear in the output.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
------=_Part_36_1630809987.1777536509560--
